International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

[1]
Date: Thu 1 Sep 2016
Source: O Hoje [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.ohoje.com.br/noticia/cidades/n/122919/t/febre-amarela-mata-75-das-vitimas-em-goias


Yellow fever has killed 75 percent of the people who contracted the disease in Goias in the period between January 2015 and August 2016. There were 8 confirmed cases. Of these, just 2 people survived according to the State Secretariat of Health (SES).

These SES numbers did not include a death in Goias that is still under investigation by the agency, but was confirmed by tests of the Municipal Secretariat of Health (SMS). The number takes into account the death of a 27-year-old man who resided in the Northeastern Region of the capital, with a case fatality rate of 77 percent.

In 2015, the cases were concentrated in Goias North Region, in the municipalities such as São Miguel and Alto Paraíso. This year [2016] the cases are concentrated in the center of the state. The 3 suspected cases were reported in Goiânia, Senador Canedo, and São Luiz de Montes Belos.

The Goiania SMS intensified its vaccination efforts against the disease in the capital. The SES biomedical specialist on yellow fever Helio Filho understands that this is extremely important in order to deal with a situation for which there is prevention.

He stated that the 2 cases which occurred in Goias were from the northern state of Bahia. "One of our concerns is about tourists and people from regions where vaccine coverage is not recommended, such as the Northeast Region and costal areas of the country," said Fihlo.

--
